{
  "document_id": "ps-73",
  "title": "Psalms 73",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Truly God is good to Israel,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "But as for me, my feet had almost stumbled;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "For I was envious of the arrogant;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "For they have no pain;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "They are not in trouble as others are;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "Therefore pride is their necklace;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "Their eyes swell out with fatness;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "They scoff and speak with malice;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "They set their mouths against heaven,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "Therefore the people turn and praise them"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "And they say, “How can God know?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "Such are the wicked;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "All in vain I have kept my heart clean"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "For all day long I have been plagued"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "If I had said, “I will talk on in this way,”"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "But when I thought how to understand this,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "until I went into the sanctuary of God;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "Truly you set them in slippery places;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "How they are destroyed in a moment,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "They are like a dream when one awakes;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "When my soul was embittered,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "I was stupid and ignorant;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "Nevertheless, I am continually with you;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "You guide me with your counsel,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "Whom have I in heaven but you?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "My flesh and my heart may fail,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "Indeed, those who are far from you will perish;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-73-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "But for me it is good to be near God;"
    }
  ]
}